tables.name: SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader
tables.description: The SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader table contains information related to sales orders, including details such as order dates, shipping and billing addresses, and payment specifics. This table is essential for managing and tracking sales orders from initiation through fulfillment and delivery. It includes identifiers for sales, customer, and purchase orders, as well as financial data like subtotals, taxes, and totals due. The table also provides status updates and comments for each order, facilitating comprehensive order management and analysis.

columns.name: SalesOrderID
columns.definition: The SalesOrderID column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader table is an integer type that serves as the primary key for the table. Each value in this column uniquely identifies a sales order record and ensures that each order can be distinctly referenced. The SalesOrderID is generated and assigned upon the creation of a new sales order entry, making it a crucial identifier for querying and managing sales order data.

columns.name: RevisionNumber
columns.definition: The RevisionNumber column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader table is a tiny integer that indicates the version or revision level of a sales order. This column helps track changes or updates made to a sales order, with higher numbers representing more recent revisions. It is important for maintaining historical accuracy and ensuring that the most current information about a sales order is available.

columns.name: OrderDate
columns.definition: The OrderDate column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader table contains the date when the sales order was created. This column holds datetime values, reflecting the specific day and time the order was placed. It is used to track and sort orders based on when they were initiated. Filtering or searching by this column allows for analysis of order patterns over time.

columns.name: DueDate
columns.definition: The DueDate column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader table contains datetime values representing the date by which a sales order is expected to be fulfilled. It is used to track deadlines for order completion and delivery. This column is useful for filtering orders based on their expected completion dates to monitor timeliness and manage logistics.

columns.name: ShipDate
columns.definition: The ShipDate column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader table represents the date and time when the order was shipped to the customer. This column is of datetime type and records the actual shipping date for each sales order. It is crucial for tracking the fulfillment and delivery process of orders.

columns.name: Status
columns.definition: The Status column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader table is used to indicate the current state of a sales order. The data in this column is stored as a tinyint, representing different stages of the order process such as pending, completed, or canceled. The values in this column help to track and manage the order's lifecycle from creation to fulfillment or cancellation. This column is essential for identifying the progress and final status of each sales order in the system.

columns.name: OnlineOrderFlag
columns.definition: The OnlineOrderFlag column is a bit data type in the SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader table. It indicates whether the sales order was placed online. A value of 1 (true) means the order was made online, while a value of 0 (false) means it was not. This column is used to distinguish between online and offline orders for reporting and analysis purposes.

columns.name: SalesOrderNumber
columns.definition: The SalesOrderNumber column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader table stores unique identifiers for each sales order in the form of alphanumeric strings. These identifiers typically start with the prefix 'SO' followed by a series of numeric digits. The SalesOrderNumber is not a primary key but is used to uniquely identify and track sales orders within the system for referencing and processing. It ensures that each sales order can be distinctly recognized and managed.

columns.name: PurchaseOrderNumber
columns.definition: The PurchaseOrderNumber column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader table contains alphanumeric identifiers for purchase orders associated with each sales order. These values are unique to each purchase order and help in tracking and distinguishing individual orders made by customers. The data type for this column is nvarchar, indicating it includes both letters and numbers. This column is not a primary key but is used to reference purchase orders linked to the sales transactions.

columns.name: AccountNumber
columns.definition: The AccountNumber column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader table contains alphanumeric strings that uniquely identify the account associated with each sales order. The account number follows a specific format and is used to link orders to customer accounts for tracking and billing purposes. This field is essential for ensuring accurate customer account management and financial reporting.

columns.name: CustomerID
columns.definition: The CustomerID column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader table is an integer field that uniquely identifies each customer associated with a sales order. This column is used to link sales orders to specific customers, allowing for the retrieval of customer-related details and history. It is crucial for tracking customer activity and managing orders within the sales database. The CustomerID value helps in querying and filtering data based on individual customer transactions.

columns.name: ShipToAddressID
columns.definition: ShipToAddressID is an integer column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader table that contains the address ID where the order is to be shipped. This column is used to reference the specific shipping address for each sales order. The values in this column are linked to the corresponding addresses in the address table, which holds detailed address information. The column ensures that each order can be accurately shipped to the correct location.

columns.name: BillToAddressID
columns.definition: The BillToAddressID column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader table represents the identifier for the address to which the bill for the sales order is to be sent. It is an integer value that links to an address entity in the database, ensuring that each sales order has a designated billing address. This column is used to associate and retrieve specific billing details related to a given sales order.

columns.name: ShipMethod
columns.definition: The ShipMethod column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader table contains the shipment method used for delivering the sales order. This is a text field that indicates the name or type of shipping service utilized, such as a specific carrier or transport method. It helps in identifying how and by which service the order was shipped.

columns.name: CreditCardApprovalCode
columns.definition: The CreditCardApprovalCode column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader table contains unique codes that are generated during the credit card approval process for sales orders. These codes are typically alphanumeric strings provided by the credit card processor or issuing bank to confirm that the payment has been authorized. This column is used to track and verify successful credit card transactions for sales orders. Being an important part of the payment validation, it ensures that the order can be processed and shipped.

columns.name: SubTotal
columns.definition: The SubTotal column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader table represents the pre-tax amount for each sales order. It is stored as a monetary value and indicates the total cost of items ordered before any tax or freight charges are applied. This column helps in calculating the overall total due for a sales order by adding tax and freight amounts subsequently.

columns.name: TaxAmt
columns.definition: The TaxAmt column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader table represents the monetary amount of tax applied to each sales order. This column contains numeric data in the monetary format, specifying the tax levied on the order total. The values in this column are essential for calculating the total amount due for each sales order, as they contribute to the final cost alongside subtotal and freight charges.

columns.name: Freight
columns.definition: The Freight column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader table contains the shipping cost associated with each sales order. This cost is expressed in monetary terms and represents the amount charged to deliver the goods to the customer. The values are stored as money data types, indicating that they include currency symbols and decimal places for precision. This column is crucial for financial calculations and determining the total cost of fulfilling each sales order.

columns.name: TotalDue
columns.definition: The TotalDue column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader table contains the total amount that is due for each sales order. This column is of type money and is calculated by summing up the subtotal, tax amount, and freight for the order. It represents the final amount that the customer needs to pay, inclusive of any additional charges.

columns.name: Comment
columns.definition: The "Comment" column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader table stores additional textual notes or remarks related to a sales order. This column can contain any free-form text entered by the user to provide context or special instructions associated with the order. Comments may include details such as delivery preferences, customer feedback, or internal notes for the sales team. This field can be left blank if no additional information is provided.

columns.name: rowguid
columns.definition: The rowguid column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader table contains uniqueidentifier values that are used to ensure the uniqueness of each row in the table. This column is typically used for replication or to maintain row integrity across multiple systems. Each value in the rowguid column is a globally unique identifier (GUID), which guarantees that it is unique across all records and tables where it is used.

columns.name: ModifiedDate
columns.definition: The ModifiedDate column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader table stores the date and time when a particular sales order record was last updated. This column helps track the most recent changes made to the sales order details. It is of the datetime data type and does not contain any special formatting. This information can be used to filter or sort records based on their last modified timestamp.
